# OpenClaw skills

## File format (OpenClaw / AgentSkills)

- Each skill is a **folder** under `.openclaw/skills/` containing a file named **`SKILL.md`** (not `my-skill.md` at the skills root). See [OpenClaw Skills](https://docs.openclaw.ai/tools/skills.md).
- `SKILL.md` **must** begin with YAML frontmatter: the opening `---` is the **first line** (no title or prose before it).
- The `name` in frontmatter should match `skills.entries` in `openclaw.json` (e.g. `name: hhmail` ↔ `"hhmail": { "enabled": true }`).
- OpenClaw’s parser expects **single-line** frontmatter values; put `metadata` as a **one-line** JSON object when needed (e.g. `metadata: { "openclaw": { "emoji": "✉️" } }`).
- Frontmatter shape:

```yaml
---
name: [Skill Name]
description: [Brief purpose]
icon: [Emoji]
---
```

## Logic

- Put JavaScript/TypeScript inside fenced code blocks.
- Use Openclaw’s `sdk` for tool definitions and calls.
- Register or enable skills in `.openclaw/openclaw.json` under `skills` when needed; **deploy** so the remote gateway picks up changes.

## Dependencies

If a skill needs a new NPM package, verify it is available in the Openclaw Docker environment before using it.
